commentTextItems.html: on the leg stump, whips it through midwicket for a boundary to bring up a resounding victory

commentPostTextItems.html: Well that would bring some cheer to Bangladesh cricket fans as they are back to winning ways after being trounced by South Africa.
Nafees with an unbeaten 90 laid the foundation and was ably supported by his captain, Ashraful, who scored an unbeaten 64

milestones.description: This is the lowest match aggregate (371) involving teams Bangladesh & Ireland in ODIs

stories.title: Nafees and Ashraful seal big win
stories.subTitle: Bangladesh v Ireland, 1st ODI, Mirpur
stories.summary: Shahriar Nafees struck a fluent unbeaten 90 while Mohammad Ashraful signalled his return to form with 64 not out, as Bangladesh avenged their loss to Ireland in the World Cup with a convincing eight-wicket win in Mirpur

stories.title: Bangladesh keen to reverse ODI drought
stories.subTitle: Bangladesh v Ireland, 1st ODI, Mirpur
stories.summary: While Ireland have little to lose, the pressure is very much on Bangladesh, who since their meeting in the World Cup have lost all 12 ODIs they have played

stories.title: Ireland promise to play 'good cricket'
stories.subTitle: Ireland in Bangladesh 2007-08
stories.summary: Ireland arrived for their first tour of Bangladesh promising to play good cricket during the three-ODI series which gets underway on Tuesday
